types of wallet

1. Hot wallets           = online
2. Cold wallets          = offline

** app kise v cryptocurrencies ko hot/cold dono hi wallet m rakh skte ho.


1. Hot wallets           = online rhta h, hamesa isme access lgta h, y fir  aap treding krte ho.to useally hot wallet m apni assessts rakhte ho.
   >> hot wallet m utne hi rakhe jitne aap trading k liye use krte ho.

2. cold wallets           = offline rhta h, isliya isme Hacking k chance bht kam hote h.
   >> for long-term holding k liye aap hamesa cold wallet m hi assessts rakhe.

3. Hot Wallets vs Cold Wallets difference :-

Feature	                         Hot Wallets	                                                           Cold Wallets
i) Internet Connection	         Ye hamesha internet se connected rehte hain.	                           Ye internet se connected nahi hote (Offline).

ii) Easy of Use	                  inse funds transfer karna bahut aasaan aur fast hai.	                   Inme transfer karne ke liye extra steps lene padte hain.

iii) Security	                   Internet se jude hone ke karan inme hacking ka khatra rehta hai.	       Inme hacking ke chances bahut hi kam hote hain.

iv) Examples                        Mobile wallets, Web wallets, aur Desktop wallets.                           Hardware wallets (USB jaisa device) aur Paper wallets.


- Hardware wallet apko buy krn hota h.
- paper waigra apko free m mil jata h,isko aap easily download or use kr skte ho, but y sab cryptocurrencies k liye avilable ni h.


